{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01EGjyerEUt3ZFyxyryQPT1i","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both client deployments rolled out successfully and the new pods are `1/1 Running`. The task is complete.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Diagnosis** (before fixing):\n- `/app`: `app-user` had an **empty configure** permission (broken); `ops-user` held **full permissions on /app** (scoping violation — it should have none).\n- `/ops`: `ops-user` had **no permissions at all** (broken); only `admin` was present.\n\n**Fixes applied** (via `rabbitmqctl`):\n- `set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — gave app-user full configure/write/read on /app.\n- `clear_permissions -p /app ops-user` — removed the misplaced grant.\n- `set_permissions -p /ops ops-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — gave ops-user full access on /ops.\n- `clear_permissions -p /ops app-user` — ensured app-user has nothing on /ops.\n\n**End state verified:**\n- `/app`: `app-user` `.* .* .*`, no ops-user. `/ops`: `ops-user` `.* .* .*`, no app-user. ✅ Each user scoped to only its own vhost.\n- `app-client` and `ops-client` both `1/1 Running`. ✅\n- Cluster healthy with 3 running nodes (rabbitmq-0/1/2). ✅\n\nOnly native kubectl/rabbitmqctl was used — no CRD, Operator, or third-party controller."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":648,"cache_read_input_tokens":30114,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":648},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"370d2b7b-b830-40be-be76-f5818f7fe8d9","uuid":"833fc73a-54d5-41db-857e-e52c7b2118fa","request_id":"req_011CcAYp6RMEQDsyn6VwiEaE"}
